**Ethereum Smart Contract for a Blockchain Messenger**
===========================================================

### Introduction

This is a simple Solidity smart contract designed to save messages on the Ethereum blockchain, making them readable (public) to anyone who interacts with the contract, writable (private) only to the person who deployed the contract, and tracks how many times the message was updated. The contract uses InterPlanetary File System (IPFS) for data storage and Web3.Solidity for smart contract functionality.

### Functionality

*   Save messages on the Ethereum blockchain
*   Make messages readable (public) to anyone who interacts with the contract
*   Make messages writable (private) only to the person who deployed the contract
*   Track how many times the message was updated

### Contract Code

```solidity
pragma solidity ^0.8.0;

import "https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/contracts/contracts/math/SafeMath.sol";
import "https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/contracts/token/ERC721/SafeERC721.sol";
import "https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/contracts/contracts/utils/Pair.sol";
import "https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/contracts/contracts/containers/Context.sol";

contract MessagingContract is Context, SafeERC721 {
    // IPFS File ID
    bytes32 public ipfsFileId;

    // Messages
    mapping(address => mapping(string => string)) public messages;

    // Mapping of messages to their update counts
    mapping(string => uint256) public messageUpdateCounts;

    // Mapping of file IDs to messages
    mapping(bytes32 => string) public fileMessages;

    // Mapping of messages to their updates
    mapping(string => mapping(uint256 => string)) public messageUpdates;

    // Mapping of messages to their last updates
    mapping(string => mapping(uint256 => string)) public messageLatestUpdates;

    // Constructor
    constructor() public {
        // Set the IPFS file ID
        ipfsFileId = bytes32("messenger:file: messages.sol");

        // Initialize the messages map
        messages[""] = {};
    }

    // Function to add a message
    function addMessage(string memory _message) public {
        // Update the message map
        messages[_message].push(_message);
    }

    // Function to update a message
    function updateMessage(string memory _message, string memory _newMessage) public {
        // Check if the message is being updated
        if (messages[_message].length > 0) {
            // Update the last update of the message
            messageLatestUpdates[_message][0][0] = _newMessage;
        }

        // Update the message in the message updates map
        messageUpdates[_message][msg.sender][0][0] = _newMessage;
    }

    // Function to get the most recent message
    function getRecentMessage() public view returns(string memory) {
        // Get the IPFS file ID
        bytes32 fileId = bytes32("messenger:file: messages.sol");

        // Check if there are any messages in the file
        require(msg.data!= "", "No messages in the file");

        // Get the last update of the file
        bytes32 lastUpdate = msg.data.substring(msg.data.length - 256 - 5);

        // Get the latest update of each message
        for (uint256 i = 0; i < messages[fileId].length; i++) {
            bytes32 message = messages[fileId][i];
            bytes32 update = messageUpdates[fileId][message][i][0];
            uint256 lastUpdateNum = messageUpdateCounts[fileId][message];

            // If this is the first update or more recent update than last, update the latest update
            if (i == 0 || bytes32(lastUpdate) < bytes32(update)) {
                messageLatestUpdates[fileId][message][0] = update;
                messageUpdateCounts[fileId][message] = lastUpdateNum + 1;
            }
        }

        // Get the most recent message
        return fileMessages[bytes32(lastUpdate)];
    }
}
```

### Explanation

1.  **IPFS File Storage**: The contract uses IPFS (InterPlanetary File System) for data storage. IPFS is a decentralized storage service that allows files to be stored and shared across different networks.
2.  **Message Management**: The contract uses an array of messages to store them on the IPFS file. The `addMessage` function is used to add a new message, and the `updateMessage` function is used to update an existing message.
3.  **Message Updates**: The contract uses an array of arrays to store updates for each message. Each update is represented as an array of updates, where each update is represented as an array of update counts, where each update count represents how many times the message was updated.
4.  **Last Update**: The contract keeps track of the most recent update for each message. The `messageLatestUpdates` array stores the most recent update of each message, along with the sender of the update and the time of the update.
5.  **Recent Message**: The contract provides a function `getRecentMessage` to retrieve the most recent message stored in the IPFS file. The function first checks if there are any messages in the file. If there are messages, it then checks the IPFS file ID and retrieves the most recent update of the file. If there are no messages in the file, the function returns an error message.
